{"title_page": "Joan of Arc (disambiguation)", "text_new": "'''[[Joan of Arc]]''' (1412\u20131431) was a French woman who is known for her role in the Hundred Years' War and as a religious figure.\n\n'''Joan of Arc''' may also refer to:\n{{TOC right}}\n==Film and television==\n* [[Joan of Arc (1900 film)|''Joan of Arc'' (1900 film)]]\n* ''[[The Passion of Joan of Arc]]'' (1928 film)\n* [[Joan of Arc (1935 film)|''Joan of Arc'' (1935 film)]]\n* [[Joan of Arc (1948 film)|''Joan of Arc'' (1948 film)]]\n* [[Joan of Arc (miniseries)|''Joan of Arc'' (miniseries)]] (1999 television miniseries)\n* ''[[The Messenger: The Story of Joan of Arc]]'', a 1999 historical drama film\n* [[Joan of Arc (2019 film)|''Joan of Arc'' (2019 film)]]\n\n==Music==\n* [[Joan of Arc (band)]], an American indie band\n* [[Joan of Arc (album)|''Joan of Arc'' (album)]], an album by Tony Conrad\n* [[Joan of Arc (Leonard Cohen song)|\"Joan of Arc\" (Leonard Cohen song)]]\n* [[Joan of Arc (Little Mix song)|\"Joan of Arc\" (Little Mix song)]]\n* [[Joan of Arc (Madonna song)|\"Joan of Arc\" (Madonna song)]]\n* [[Joan of Arc (Orchestral Manoeuvres in the Dark song)|\"Joan of Arc\" (Orchestral Manoeuvres in the Dark song)]]\n* \"Joan of Arc\", a 2013 song by Arcade Fire from ''[[Reflektor]]''\n* \"Joan of Arc\", a 2017 song by In This Moment from [[Ritual (In This Moment album)|''Ritual'']]\n* \"Joan of Arc\", a 1993 song by the Melvins from ''[[Houdini (album)|Houdini]]''\n\n==Other uses==\n* [[Joan of Arc (poem)|\"Joan of Arc\" (poem)]], a 1796 epic poem by Robert Southey\n* ''[[Joan of Arc: The Image of Female Heroism]]'', a book by Marina Warner\n* [[St. Joan of Arc Chapel]]\n\n==See also==\n* [[Arc (disambiguation)]]\n* [[Cultural depictions of Joan of Arc]]\n* [[Jeanne d'Arc (disambiguation)]]\n* [[Joan (disambiguation)]]\n* [[Order of St. Joan D'Arc Medallion]], a U.S. Army award\n* [[Sainte-Jeanne-d'Arc (disambiguation)]]\n* [[Joan Van Ark]], American actress\n\n{{Disambiguation}}\n", "text_old": "'''[[Joan of Arc]]''' (1412\u20131431) was a French woman who is known for her role in the Hundred Years' War and as a religious figure.\n\n'''Joan of Arc''' may also refer to:\n{{TOC right}}\n==Film and television==\n* [[Joan of Arc (1900 film)|''Joan of Arc'' (1900 film)]]\n* [[Joan of Arc (1928 film)|''Joan of Arc'' (1928 film)]]\n* [[Joan of Arc (1935 film)|''Joan of Arc'' (1935 film)]]\n* [[Joan of Arc (1948 film)|''Joan of Arc'' (1948 film)]]\n* [[Joan of Arc (miniseries)|''Joan of Arc'' (miniseries)]], a 1999 television miniseries\n* ''[[The Messenger: The Story of Joan of Arc]]'', a 1999 historical drama film\n* [[Joan of Arc (2019 film)|''Joan of Arc'' (2019 film)]]\n\n==Music==\n* [[Joan of Arc (band)]], an American indie band\n* [[Joan of Arc (album)|''Joan of Arc'' (album)]], an album by Tony Conrad\n* [[Joan of Arc (Leonard Cohen song)|\"Joan of Arc\" (Leonard Cohen song)]]\n* [[Joan of Arc (Little Mix song)|\"Joan of Arc\" (Little Mix song)]]\n* [[Joan of Arc (Madonna song)|\"Joan of Arc\" (Madonna song)]]\n* [[Joan of Arc (Orchestral Manoeuvres in the Dark song)|\"Joan of Arc\" (Orchestral Manoeuvres in the Dark song)]]\n* \"Joan of Arc\", a 2013 song by Arcade Fire from ''[[Reflektor]]''\n* \"Joan of Arc\", a 2017 song by In This Moment from [[Ritual (In This Moment album)|''Ritual'']]\n* \"Joan of Arc\", a 1993 song by the Melvins from ''[[Houdini (album)|Houdini]]''\n\n==Other uses==\n* [[Joan of Arc (poem)|\"Joan of Arc\" (poem)]], a 1796 epic poem by Robert Southey\n* ''[[Joan of Arc: The Image of Female Heroism]]'', a book by Marina Warner\n* [[St. Joan of Arc Chapel]]\n\n==See also==\n* [[Arc (disambiguation)]]\n* [[Cultural depictions of Joan of Arc]]\n* [[Jeanne d'Arc (disambiguation)]]\n* [[Joan (disambiguation)]]\n* [[Order of St. Joan D'Arc Medallion]], a U.S. Army award\n* [[Sainte-Jeanne-d'Arc (disambiguation)]]\n* [[Joan Van Ark]], American actress\n\n{{Disambiguation}}\n", "name_user": "Gohst", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200e