ony Nicholl]]<ref>Nicholl was disabled from sitting by an order in January 1648, but this was revoked in June 1648.</ref>||rowspan=\"3\"| [[Roundhead|Parliamentarian]] \n|-\n|January 1644\n|colspan=\"3\"|''Arundel disabled from sitting - seat vacant''\n|-\n|1648\n|style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Thomas Waller (MP for Bodmin)|Thomas Waller]]||\n|-\n|December 1648\n|colspan=\"3\"|''Waller excluded in [[Pride's Purge]] - seat vacant''||colspan=\"3\"|''Nichols not known to have sat after [[Pride's Purge]]''\n|-\n|1653\n|colspan=\"6\"|''Bodmin was unrepresented in the [[Barebones Parliament]] and the [[First Protectorate Parliament|First]] and [[Second Protectorate Parliament|Second]] Parliaments of the Protectorate''\n|-\n|[[Third Protectorate Parliament|January 1659]] \n|style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[John Silly]]  ||<!-- party -->\n|style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[William Turner (MP for Bodmin)|William Turner]] ||<!-- party -->\n|-\n|[[Rump Parliament|May 1659]]\n|colspan=\"6\"|''Not represented in the restored [[Rump Parliament|Rump]]''\n|-\n|April 1660\n|rowspan=\"3\" style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n|rowspan=\"3\"| [[Hender Robartes]]\n|rowspan=\"3\"| <!-- party -->\n|style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[John Silly]]\n| <!-- party -->\n|-\n| 1661\n|style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Sir John Carew, 3rd Baronet|Sir John Carew]]\n| <!-- party -->\n|-\n| 1679\n|rowspan=\"3\" style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n|rowspan=\"3\"| [[Nicholas Glynn]]\n|rowspan=\"3\"| <!-- party -->\n|-\n| 1689\n|style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Sir John Cutler, 1st Baronet|Sir John Cutler Bt]]\n| <!-- party -->\n|-\n| 1693\n|rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n|rowspan=\"2\"| [[Russell Robartes]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"| <!-- party -->\n|-\n| 1695\n|rowspan=\"3\" style=\"background-color: {{Tories (British political party)/meta/color}}\" |\n|rowspa