in by-election|By-election, 13 August 1859]]: Bodmin<ref name=\"craig1832\"/>}}\n{{Election box candidate unopposed with party link|\n |party = Liberal Party (UK)\n |candidate = [[James Wyld]]\n}}\n{{Election box gain with party link no swing|\n  |winner     = Liberal Party (UK)\n  |loser = Conservative Party (UK)\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n<small>[[#Elections|Back to elections]]</small>\n\n===Elections in the 1860s===\n{{Election box begin | title=[[1865 United Kingdom general election|General election 1865]]: Bodmin (2 seats)<ref name=\"craig1832\"/>}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n |party =Liberal Party (UK)\n |candidate = [[Frederick Leveson-Gower (Bodmin MP)|Frederick Leveson-Gower]]\n |votes = 263\n |percentage = 42.8\n |change = +5.7\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n |party = Liberal Party (UK)\n |candidate = [[James Wyld]]\n |votes = 238\n |percentage = 38.7\n |change = +9.9\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n |party = Conservative Party (UK)\n |candidate = Charles Locock Webb<ref name=\"clwebb\"/>\n |votes = 114\n |percentage = 18.5\n |change = &minus;15.6\n}}\n{{Election box majority|\n |votes = 124\n |percentage = 20.2\n |change = +17.3\n}} \n{{Election box turnout|\n |votes = 365 (est)\n |percentage = 91.8 (est)\n |change = +17.4\n}}\n{{Election box registered electors|\n |reg. electors = 397\n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link|\n  |winner     = Liberal Party (UK)\n  |swing      = +6.8\n}}\n{{Election box gain with party link|\n  |winner     = Liberal Party (UK)\n  |loser = Conservative Party (UK)\n  |swing      = +8.9\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\nThe seat was reduced to one member for the 1868 election.\n\n{{Election box begin | title=[[1868 United Kingdom general election|General election 1868]]: Bodmin<ref name=\"craig1832\"/>}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n |party =Liberal Party (UK)\n |candidate = [[Frederick Leveson-Gower (Bodmin MP)|Frederick Leveson-Gower]]\n |votes = 424\n |percentage